[start section id="20103"]

Mr. Vestal is an 83-year-old male who was recently found to have a transverse colon mass. He had a CT-scan showed both a transverse colon mass and a right colon mass, biopsy-proven adenocarcinoma.  He is now here for surgical resection. Risks, benefits, alternatives, indications, procedure, team approach and advance directives discussed with the patient and he wishes to proceed with surgery.

